tiano nuevo judaizante, adversario de la Iglesia, o más bien un creyente ortodoxo que, inspirado en ideales sociales, pretendía dirigir una severa crítica contra la moral degenerada de ciertas clases ociosas en la sociedad de su tiempo?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh1 aEdel, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2020z9783110689631oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396869029240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783968690292423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783968690292.jpg  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020